column5: i lol'd   i love when it gets caught on his pants lol  <object width="425" height="344"><param name="movie" value="
Thats no real test give the lures to Lew and he could give them a real test.
Speaking of Lew, where has he been? I haven't seen any recent posts from him lately?
gone for the summer....back in October....
Lew is living the life right now but i might run into him this weekend.
We usually see some updates from Lew when he heads back to TO to take care of things...  Mike
you could tell that guy was having a lot of fun smacking those lures off the ground
Dang it i was hoping he would hook himself

Since he has a vested interest in the Super D i wonder how hard he was "straightening" out the competitions lure when it ventured off camera several times???  Personally i would think using the lures head to head and keeping a running tally of the damage after every fish might seem more prone to deliver the message ...after all ...how much damage can a lure get if it doesn't catch fish ...  just my .02

I usually try not to hit the rocks when I'm casting my musky baits??? And despite what some of my fishing partners will tell you, I have never repeatedly cast onto the middle of someones driveway.  Valid test.
man we have built thousands over the years. that is a very different way. maybe he should flog a horse
